quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  29,7,"And as to those who shall have believed and done the things that are right, their evil deeds will we surely blot out from them, and according to their best actions will we surely reward them"
  29,8,"Moreover we have enjoined on man to shew kindness to parents: but if they strive with thee that thou join that with Me of which thou hast no knowledge, obey them not. To me do ye return, and then will I tell you of your doings"
  29,9,"And those who shall have believed and done the things that are right, we will surely give them an entering in among the just"
  29,10,"But some men say, \"We believe in God,\" yet when they meet with sufferings in the cause of God, they regard trouble from man as chastisement from God. Yet if a success come from thy Lord they are sure to say, \"We were on your side!\" Doth not God well know what is in the breasts of his creatures"
  29,11,"Yes, and God well knoweth those who believe, and He well knoweth the Hypocrites"
  29,12,"The unbelievers say to the faithful, \"Follow ye our way, and we will surely bear your sins.\" But not aught of their sins will they bear - verily they are liars"
  29,13,"But their own burdens, and burdens beside their own burdens shall they surely bear: and inquisition shall be made of them on the day of Resurrection as to their false devices"
  29,14,"Of old sent we Noah to his people: a thousand years save fifty did he tarry among them; and the flood overtook them in their wrongful doings"